</style>

<div class="top-bar">
    <ul class="title-area">
        <li class="name"><span class="att-topbar-title">Getting Started</span></li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div id="att-getstarted-content">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="small-12 columns">
            <ol class="att-ol-txt" type="1">
                <li><p>Complete all the setup tasks defined in the <a href="https://attiotkitdevstorage.blob.core.windows.net/attiotkitdevdocumentation/GettingStartedGuide_ATT_IOT_rv1-3.pdf">AT&T IoT Starter Kit  Getting Started Guide</a>.</p></li>
                <li><p>Download the <a href="~/mBed/ATT_Cellular_IOT_K64F.bin">ATT_IoTStarterKit_AzureAnalyticsDemo.bin</a> file.</p></li>
                <li><p>Connect the USB cable from your laptop to the FRDM-K64F board to force a board power cycle.  (If already connected, disconnect, and then reconnect). Wait for the MBED drive to enumerate.</p></li>
                <li><p>Once the MBED drive is enumerated, drag and drop the ATT_IoTStarterKit_AzureAnalyticsDemo.bin you just downloaded to the MBED drive.</p></li>
            </ol>
            <p>
                <button class="att-button" id="home_Btn" onclick="window.location = '/home'">Home</button>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
